Many mail clients block http references to images in HTML notifications, until the user explicitly enables images for the mail. This would not be a big deal (the images don't add much) but in Outlook, the formatting of the mail without images is broken. The left bar containing key, type, priority etc. is very wide, and the right bar containing summary etc. is narrow.

We should see if a simple fix (eg. specifying width and height in the <img> tags) can fix this formatting.

